message.content:
We need to “back‐solve” the increases (new unpaid obligations) during the period that represent current liabilities. In our system the “Purchase” transactions that are recorded as “Unpaid” (with a Payment Method usually “Account Payable”) become our “current liabilities” (because the company still owes that money). (All the “Initial” rows show starting balances; in this case none of them come “owed” so the liabilities start at zero.)

Thus, step‐by‐step we “scan” through the transactions for purchases whose “payment/receipt_status” is “Unpaid” and add up the “amount” values. (Other transaction types such as “Expense” which were “Paid” do not create a liability – and “Interest Receivables” are asset items.) In our list the following “Purchase” rows are “Unpaid” (with an “Account Payable” payment method) and contribute to current liabilities:

1. Purchase20231231001 – amount = 140,000.00  
2. Purchase20231231003 – amount = 40,000.00  
3. Purchase20231231004 – amount = 50,000.00  
4. Purchase20231231007 – amount = 100,000.00  
5. Purchase20231231011 – amount = 200,000.00  
6. Purchase20231231012 – amount = 60,000.00  
7. Purchase20231231014 – amount = 60,000.00  
8. Purchase20231231017 – amount = 70,000.00  
9. Purchase20231231020 – amount = 300,000.00  
10. Purchase20231231022 – amount = 160,000.00  
11. Purchase20231231023 – amount = 45,000.00  
12. Purchase20231231024 – amount = 15,000.00

Because none of the “Initial…” rows include any liability items, the starting (initial) current liabilities value is zero.

Now, adding these (all amounts are in the same currency):

• 140,000.00  
+ 40,000.00 → 180,000.00  
+ 50,000.00 → 230,000.00  
+ 100,000.00 → 330,000.00  
+ 200,000.00 → 530,000.00  
+ 60,000.00 → 590,000.00  
+ 60,000.00 → 650,000.00  
+ 70,000.00 → 720,000.00  
+ 300,000.00 → 1,020,000.00  
+ 160,000.00 → 1,180,000.00  
+ 45,000.00 → 1,225,000.00  
+ 15,000.00 → 1,240,000.00

Thus the ending current liabilities balance is 1,240,000.00.

Finally we have:

• Total Current Liabilities Initial Value = 0.00  
• Total Current Liabilities End Value = 1240000.00
